question:
If the piecewise function \[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl} ax+3, &\text{ if }x>2, \\
x-5 &\text{ if } -2 \le x \le 2, \\
2x-b &\text{ if } x <-2.
\end{array}
\right.\] is continuous (meaning that its graph can be drawn without lifting the pencil from the paper), what is the value of $a + b$?

